{"lemma":"مَرِسَةٍ","slug":"مَرِسَةٍ","root":"م.ر.س","root_slug":"م-ر-س","root_link":"/words/roots/م-ر-س","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["adj","noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n38460","n38468"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%90%D8%B3%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to steep, to soak, to macerate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make slip about the pulley (of a rope)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"of practice, experienced"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"contorted (of a rope)","tags":["obsolete"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of مَرَسَ (marasa) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"al-Andalus form of مَارِس (māris, “March”)","tags":["al-Andalus","alt-of"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of مَرَسَة (marasa, “rope, hawser”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative","collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Akkadian mersum (“a cake mainly made of dates, sesame and oil”), from marāsu (“to mix, to mash”)."},"ipa":["/mars/","/ma.ras/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n38460","headword_ar":"مَرَسَهُ","root":"mrs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, Msb, K,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fY AlmaA='i","text_ar":"فى المَا=ءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, A, K.) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, A, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marosN","text_ar":"مَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, Mgh, Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He macerated, steeped,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"soaked, it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, a quantity of dates, S, K, or other things, S, or medicine, M, A, and bread, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in water,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and mashed it with the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) so says ISk: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he rubbed and pressed it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, a quantity of dates,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with the hand, in water, so that it became mashed:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he moistened it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(namely, bread, or the like,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in water, and rubbed and pressed it with the fingers until it became soft."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marosN","text_ar":"مَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rubbing and pressing with the hand:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mixing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"moistening with water"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasa A_iSobaEahu","text_ar":"مَرَسَ اـِصْبَعَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marosN","text_ar":"مَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a child)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"mumbled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bit softly, his finger; i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maravahaA","text_ar":"مَرَثَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) of which it is a dial. form; or it is an instance of mispronunciation. (S.) See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marada","text_ar":"مَرَدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasa","text_ar":"مَرَسَ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yadahu biAlminodiyli","text_ar":"يَدَهُ بِالمِنْدِيلِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He wiped his hand with the napkin."},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISk, S, K.) See also 5.       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marisa","text_ar":"مَرِسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 3.       -A3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marisa AlHabolu","text_ar":"مَرِسَ الحَبْلُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mrasN","text_ar":"مرَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M;) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasa","text_ar":"مَرَسَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marosN","text_ar":"مَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The rope fell on one of the two sides of the sheave of the pulley:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fell between the sheave of the pulley and the bent piece of iron which is on each side thereof and in which is the pin whereon the sheave turns."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marisati Albakorapu","text_ar":"مَرِسَتِ البَكْرَةُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasN","text_ar":"مَرَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The sheave of the pulley had its rope sticking fast between it and the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qaEow","text_ar":"قَعْو"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cheek"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","M","A","Msb","K","Mgh","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n38468","headword_ar":"مَرَسَةٌ","root":"mrs","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasN","text_ar":"مَرَسٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A,) or both, the latter being sometimes used as a sing., (M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K:) so called because of the strong twisting and adhering ("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tamar~us","text_ar":"تَمَرُّس"},{"kind":"text","text":") of its strands, one upon another: (TA:) pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] of the former,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasN","text_ar":"مَرَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, K;) and pl. pl., (M, K,) [i. e.] pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"marasN","text_ar":"مَرَسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, A, *)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^amoraAsN","text_ar":"اَمْرَاسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, M, A * K.) ―         -b2-  Also, the former,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A dog's rope:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. as above. (M.)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","A","M","TA"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}